              <span id="reviewTextContainer3551247327" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14736707110372051437">What stands out to my mind is just how beautifully and subtly this is written. Loved the visual descriptions of a country and way of life that is difficult for me to imagine.<br/><br/>Set around three characters, the aging novelist Oki, his ex mistress Otoko and the young protege Keiko. In some ways the sadness overshadowed the beauty element in this story. Dark themes on offer and an ending that I found wanting but fitting at the same time.</span>

