      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/8550.Yasunari_Kawabata">About Yasunari Kawabata</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/8550.Yasunari_Kawabata"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1235793826p3/8550.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/8550.Yasunari_Kawabata">Yasunari Kawabata
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
2,598
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer2926780095647393573">Yasunari <b>Kawabata</b> (<a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/846386._' rel='nofollow noopener'>川端 康成</a>) was a Japanese short story writer and novelist whose spare, lyrical, subtly-shaded prose works won him the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1968, the first Japanese author to receive the award. His works have enjoyed broad international appeal and are still widely read today.<br/><br/>Nobel Lecture: 1968<br/><a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/literature/laureates/1968/kawabata-lecture.html'>http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prize...</a></span>
  <span id="freeText2926780095647393573" style="display:none">Yasunari <b>Kawabata</b> (<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/846386._" rel="nofollow noopener">川端 康成</a>) was a Japanese short story writer and novelist whose spare, lyrical, subtly-shaded prose works won him the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1968, the first Japanese author to receive the award. His works have enjoyed broad international appeal and are still widely read today.<br /><br />Nobel Lecture: 1968<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/literature/laureates/1968/kawabata-lecture.html">http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prize...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="2926780095647393573" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

<div class="clear"></div></div></div><div class="bigBoxBottom"></div></div>

  

